WEBVTT

00:01.977 --> 00:03.710
Clarence: Mom, Chad, and Jeff
were looking for me in storm.

00:03.712 --> 00:05.712
Also, Sumo and his dad
tried to find a baby badger.

00:05.714 --> 00:07.146
Then Mr. Reese and Belson
tried to find Ms. Baker,

00:07.148 --> 00:08.748
but I was with her
at the Nite Bites.

00:08.750 --> 00:10.416
Also,
Ms. Shoop played basketball.

00:10.418 --> 00:14.053
And now everybody's stuck
in the gym.

00:14.055 --> 00:15.088
[ Remote clicks ]

00:15.090 --> 00:16.623
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:18.960 --> 00:21.894
♪ I don't care what you say! ♪

00:22.230 --> 00:25.732
[ Thunder crashing ]

00:32.440 --> 00:36.643
♪♪

00:38.280 --> 00:39.579
Oh, dang.

00:39.581 --> 00:41.847
Your mom's gonna
bake my meatloaf.

00:41.849 --> 00:43.483
I just don't know
where he could be.

00:43.485 --> 00:45.251
We should go back out there
and find him.

00:45.253 --> 00:47.487
No,
it's too dangerous.

00:47.489 --> 00:50.423
I'm sure he's f-f...
[Sobbing] fine!

00:50.425 --> 00:51.925
[ Sobs ]

00:51.927 --> 00:54.994
Sumo, shield your eyes
from the grown man's tears.

00:54.996 --> 00:57.597
Have you guys seen Clarence?
Negative.

00:57.599 --> 00:59.265
[ Groans ]

00:59.267 --> 01:01.100
I know
how you feel.

01:01.102 --> 01:02.602
We can't find Candice.

01:02.604 --> 01:04.337
Candice?
- My badger.

01:04.339 --> 01:06.673
My sweet,
sharp-mouthed badger.

01:06.675 --> 01:09.442
We'll keep searching
once the storm passes.

01:09.444 --> 01:11.477
I'm sure
I'll see Candice again.

01:11.479 --> 01:14.781
If not in this life,
then in the next.

01:14.783 --> 01:16.616
That was beautiful,
son.

01:16.618 --> 01:18.217
[ Whimpering ]
- Huh?

01:18.219 --> 01:19.619
[ Whimpering continues ]

01:19.621 --> 01:22.522
Sumo, let's go stand
someplace else.

01:22.524 --> 01:24.290
[ All sobbing ]

01:24.292 --> 01:26.225
Why,
I oughta!

01:26.227 --> 01:27.327
Huh?
- Huh?            Huh?

01:27.329 --> 01:29.295
Huh?

01:29.297 --> 01:31.064
[ Chuckles ]
Uh, hi.

01:31.066 --> 01:32.832
[ Groans ]

01:32.834 --> 01:34.867
Oh, boo.
It's the mayor.

01:34.869 --> 01:36.903
I hate
that guy now.

01:36.905 --> 01:37.903
[ Stammers ]

01:37.905 --> 01:39.139
He ate
all the chips.

01:39.141 --> 01:40.873
What's a sleepover
without chips?

01:40.875 --> 01:42.675
My boy!
Oh, you're alive!

01:42.677 --> 01:44.243
[ Laughing ]
Oh, Clarence!

01:44.245 --> 01:45.878
I'll never, ever leave you
again! You hear me, my only boy?

01:45.880 --> 01:47.547
I am so glad
you're okay!

01:47.549 --> 01:48.881
Hey, Mom.

01:48.883 --> 01:50.850
W-W-Where were you,
Clarence?

01:50.852 --> 01:51.985
Oh.

01:51.987 --> 01:55.088
My favorite --
a slurpee raisin drink.

01:55.090 --> 01:56.322
[ Slurps ]

01:56.324 --> 01:57.691
Thanks, pal.

01:57.693 --> 01:59.892
Hey, did you bring that kite
you were talking about?

01:59.894 --> 02:03.229
'Cause sleepovers are pretty fun
with kites, too.

02:03.231 --> 02:04.430
No.

02:04.432 --> 02:06.366
For Jolly Man
hath forsaken me.

02:06.368 --> 02:08.834
[ Thunder crashes ]

02:08.836 --> 02:10.903
Oh, my Jeff,
I forgot to tell you.

02:10.905 --> 02:13.339
Ms. Baker is moving
to California,

02:13.341 --> 02:15.942
but also,
- she's<i> not</i> moving to California

02:15.944 --> 02:18.011
because
we're going to stop --

02:18.013 --> 02:20.679
Hey, don't you dare step foot
out of this gym, you hear me?

02:20.681 --> 02:21.881
Why would I
want to leave?

02:21.883 --> 02:23.216
All my friends
are here

02:23.218 --> 02:25.919
and Ms. Baker's here,
and she's gonna stay here.

02:25.921 --> 02:27.454
Out of the way,
bucko!

02:27.456 --> 02:28.855
Hey!
[ Grunting ]

02:28.857 --> 02:31.458
These blankets are mine!
For safety officers only!

02:31.460 --> 02:33.059
Brenda, we need
extra blankets.

02:33.061 --> 02:34.760
There's
too many people here.

02:34.762 --> 02:37.130
Bah! And whose fault
is that, Jim? Huh?

02:37.132 --> 02:39.532
Uh,
it's Mr. Storm's fault.

02:39.534 --> 02:41.801
Or Ms. Storm,
I guess. Uh...

02:41.803 --> 02:44.270
Aah! - Hey, hey, I see you!
Get back here!

02:44.272 --> 02:45.605
You can't leave.

02:45.607 --> 02:47.607
You have to stay here
and you have to teach us.

02:47.609 --> 02:49.042
Don't move
to California.

02:49.044 --> 02:51.277
Boys, this is real sweet,
but I have to go.

02:51.279 --> 02:53.613
I'm not needed here.
Mr. Reese: Melanie!

02:53.615 --> 02:55.415
Shoop is hogging
all the blankets!

02:55.417 --> 02:58.083
Plus, you're the<i> real</i>
safety officer, not her.

02:58.085 --> 03:00.420
Guys, listen -- Yeah,
I got this, Baker.

03:00.422 --> 03:01.921
See?

03:01.923 --> 03:04.491
Everyone, if I could have
your attention, please.

03:04.493 --> 03:07.593
[ Chuckles ] This storm
has been<i> pretty</i> crazy.

03:07.595 --> 03:11.164
We owe a round of applause
to the citizens keeping us safe.

03:11.166 --> 03:12.965
People like --
Uh, I'm sorry.

03:12.967 --> 03:14.500
What was
your name again?

03:14.502 --> 03:16.302
Oh, [Chuckles]
it's Mr. Reese.

03:16.304 --> 03:18.571
Let's hear it
for Mr. Rice, shall we,

03:18.573 --> 03:19.973
for leading us
to safety.

03:19.975 --> 03:23.243
[ Cheers and applause ]
Boo! Boo! Boo!

03:23.245 --> 03:25.178
Thank you,
but I couldn't have done it

03:25.180 --> 03:26.779
without my partner,
Belson.

03:26.781 --> 03:27.980
You see, he, uh --

03:27.982 --> 03:29.648
Ooh! Ooh!
Ooh! Ooh!

03:29.650 --> 03:30.984
[ Concerned murmuring ]

03:30.986 --> 03:33.519
The gym is
the designated safety zone.

03:33.521 --> 03:35.254
Actually,
according to my map,

03:35.256 --> 03:36.756
the gym
is the lowest point in town.

03:36.758 --> 03:39.659
The whole gym's gonna flood!

03:39.661 --> 03:40.993
Uh-oh.

03:40.995 --> 03:42.795
This is
all<i> your</i> fault!

03:42.797 --> 03:44.764
We're doomed!

03:44.766 --> 03:46.332
[ People screaming ]

03:46.334 --> 03:49.269
♪♪

03:50.439 --> 03:51.537
[ Wind howling ]

03:51.539 --> 03:53.773
[ Upbeat music playing ]

03:56.377 --> 03:58.945
We can use the mayor's
helicopter! According to my map,

03:58.947 --> 04:01.447
the cliff is the highest
and safest point in town.

04:01.449 --> 04:03.149
No,
it's too dangerous.

04:03.151 --> 04:04.317
Shame on you!

04:04.319 --> 04:07.319
We could use the chopper
to evacuate to the cliff!

04:07.321 --> 04:10.156
B-But the helicopter
is for the mayor!

04:10.158 --> 04:12.625
[ Chuckles ]
Save the mayor, everyone.

04:12.627 --> 04:14.394
But who's
gonna save<i> us?</i>

04:14.396 --> 04:16.529
Calm down,
you savages.

04:16.531 --> 04:18.464
[ Indistinct shouting ]

04:18.466 --> 04:20.833
[ Screaming ]

04:20.835 --> 04:23.035
I have
an announcement to make!

04:23.037 --> 04:24.504
Huh?    Huh?
Huh?            Huh?

04:24.506 --> 04:26.171
I caused the power outage.

04:26.173 --> 04:28.975
When I flew my kite
into some power lines,

04:28.977 --> 04:30.176
it was an accident.

04:30.178 --> 04:32.878
But my keeping it a secret
was not.

04:32.880 --> 04:36.316
I accept whatever punishment
you all deem appropriate.

04:37.318 --> 04:38.517
[ Indistinct shouting ]

04:38.519 --> 04:39.819
[ Screams ]

04:39.821 --> 04:42.488
Nobody cares?

04:42.490 --> 04:43.756
But I caused the outage!

04:43.758 --> 04:46.059
I-It's my fault
we're all gonna die!

04:46.061 --> 04:47.060
[ Chuckles ]

04:47.062 --> 04:49.329
You didn't
cause the outage, pal.

04:49.331 --> 04:53.232
Aberdale has a very unique
power system.

04:53.234 --> 04:56.269
It's really
very delicate.

04:56.271 --> 05:00.073
Aah!

05:00.075 --> 05:01.908
And whenever
there's a big storm,

05:01.910 --> 05:03.743
it completely
falls apart.

05:03.745 --> 05:05.745
It wasn't my fault.

05:05.747 --> 05:07.280
[ Chuckles ]

05:07.282 --> 05:08.748
Come on, Sumo.

05:08.750 --> 05:11.518
Everyone!

05:11.520 --> 05:13.186
Hello!
Over here!

05:13.188 --> 05:14.386
Here.

05:14.388 --> 05:15.855
Oh, thanks, Sumo.

05:15.857 --> 05:17.122
It's my dad's.

05:17.124 --> 05:18.758
[ Indistinct shouting ]

05:19.594 --> 05:21.393
[ Air horn blows ]

05:21.395 --> 05:23.028
I got something to say!

05:23.030 --> 05:25.598
Guys, we shouldn't
be fighting!

05:25.600 --> 05:27.366
All I ever wanted my whole life

05:27.368 --> 05:31.070
is just to have a big sleepover
with everyone that I love.

05:31.072 --> 05:33.272
[ Crowd murmuring ]

05:33.274 --> 05:35.274
And here we are,
so how about

05:35.276 --> 05:38.811
we all stop bickering and have
the best sleepover ever?

05:38.813 --> 05:40.079
I'm with Clarence!

05:40.081 --> 05:42.047
All this fighting
is getting us nowhere.

05:42.049 --> 05:44.117
Let's take a vote!

05:44.952 --> 05:48.087
Whoever wants
to fly to the cliff,

05:48.089 --> 05:50.489
raise your hand! Mr. Reese:
Wait a minute, I see something.

05:50.491 --> 05:52.391
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]
It's the mayor.

05:52.393 --> 05:54.393
He snuck away and is taking off
in the helicopter without us!

05:54.395 --> 05:56.796
Uh, maybe he's
gonna get help.

05:56.798 --> 05:58.331
He...he's laughing.

05:58.333 --> 05:59.566
Wait a minute,

05:59.568 --> 06:02.601
seems to be some sort of
creature in there with him.

06:02.603 --> 06:03.802
Definitely female.

06:03.804 --> 06:06.572
What?!
Give me those!

06:06.574 --> 06:08.508
Aah!

06:08.510 --> 06:12.078
It's Candice!

06:13.181 --> 06:15.814
Wow, Sumo,
- you really taught that critter

06:15.816 --> 06:18.418
to always
be prepared.

06:18.420 --> 06:19.785
[ Explosion ]

06:19.787 --> 06:23.355
♪♪

06:23.357 --> 06:25.257
[ Coughing ]

06:25.259 --> 06:26.458
Help!

06:26.460 --> 06:28.328
Hey,
the mayor's okay.

06:28.330 --> 06:29.829
We're out of options!

06:29.831 --> 06:32.798
We're doo-o-o-o-o-med!

06:32.800 --> 06:34.133
[ Screaming ]
Help me build a raft.

06:34.135 --> 06:35.601
Uh,
what are you doing?

06:35.603 --> 06:36.835
Trying to
spark a fire.

06:36.837 --> 06:38.838
Water hates fire.

06:38.840 --> 06:40.807
[ Grunting ]

06:40.809 --> 06:42.775
[ Grunting ]

06:42.777 --> 06:45.945
♪♪

06:45.947 --> 06:47.946
I mean,
of course I love Aberdale.

06:47.948 --> 06:49.482
There's no place like it.

06:49.484 --> 06:50.783
Everyone is so great.

06:50.785 --> 06:52.151
They've all been so sweet to me.

06:52.153 --> 06:53.619
I just...[ Sighs ]
[ Indistinct shouting ]

06:53.621 --> 06:55.555
Uh, geez.
- [ Screams ]

06:55.557 --> 06:57.289
What is my purpose?

06:57.291 --> 06:59.358
Oh, it's easy for<i> you.</i>

06:59.360 --> 07:01.627
Your purpose is to be
a fluffy little baby.

07:01.629 --> 07:02.861
[ Cat meows apathetically ]

07:02.863 --> 07:04.197
Ms. Baker,
Ms. Baker!

07:04.199 --> 07:06.032
You got to
get back in here!

07:06.034 --> 07:09.068
[ Screaming ]

07:11.639 --> 07:13.039
[ Groans ]

07:13.041 --> 07:15.207
Everyone, listen up!
Jim, put that fire out!

07:15.209 --> 07:16.409
Mavis, pick up that mess!

07:16.411 --> 07:18.144
Two of you,
stop choking each other.

07:18.146 --> 07:19.712
Gilben, keep up the good work.
All right, good job.

07:19.714 --> 07:21.881
And, Shoop, I believe you have
something that's mine.

07:21.883 --> 07:23.148
Oh, whatever.

07:23.150 --> 07:24.417
I don't
want this anyway.

07:24.419 --> 07:26.185
Everyone,
gather round, okay?

07:26.187 --> 07:28.521
It's a bad idea
to travel anywhere right now,

07:28.523 --> 07:30.690
so we have to keep the gym
from flooding.

07:30.692 --> 07:32.825
Yeah, right.
How do we even do that?

07:32.827 --> 07:34.226
Well, maybe, uh --

07:34.228 --> 07:35.895
Mary: Clarence,
what are you doing?

07:35.897 --> 07:37.329
[ Chuckling ]

07:37.331 --> 07:40.166
Um, we're making a giant fort
for our sleepover.

07:40.168 --> 07:41.868
[ Sighs ]
A giant fort?

07:41.870 --> 07:43.335
What? [ Gasps ] That's it!

07:43.337 --> 07:45.371
If we can make
some sort of wall together,

07:45.373 --> 07:47.507
we could keep out the water
and stop the gym from flooding!

07:47.509 --> 07:49.908
Great idea. - Uh, no, it's not.

07:49.910 --> 07:51.944
What are we gonna use
to make a wall?

07:51.946 --> 07:54.447
The hundreds
- of bags of manure in your room?

07:54.449 --> 07:55.848
[<i> Fart</i> ]

07:55.850 --> 07:57.283
I forgot about that.

07:57.285 --> 07:59.352
You have hundreds of bags
of manure in your room?

07:59.354 --> 08:01.354
What size are we talking?
10 pounds, 20?

08:01.356 --> 08:02.555
50.

08:02.557 --> 08:04.123
I had to hire a bunch of people
to transport them.

08:04.125 --> 08:06.525
[ Chuckling ] It was
an incredibly expensive prank.

08:06.527 --> 08:07.760
That's perfect!

08:07.762 --> 08:09.394
Okay, we'll make a levee
from those bags of manure.

08:09.396 --> 08:10.863
Uh, we need to work together.

08:10.865 --> 08:12.599
Tell us what to do,
Melanie.

08:12.601 --> 08:14.700
[ All cheering ]

08:14.702 --> 08:17.704
♪♪

08:18.540 --> 08:20.940
♪ Work it out, take command ♪

08:20.942 --> 08:22.375
[ Whistle blows ]

08:22.377 --> 08:24.043
♪ Build it up
and work the plan ♪

08:24.045 --> 08:25.277
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

08:25.279 --> 08:27.614
♪ Wah-ooh-wah ♪

08:27.616 --> 08:28.881
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

08:28.883 --> 08:31.149
♪ Wah-ooh-wah ♪

08:31.151 --> 08:34.153
♪ Pass it on, tie it tight ♪

08:34.155 --> 08:37.490
♪ If it's dark,
let's make it bright ♪

08:37.492 --> 08:38.724
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

08:38.726 --> 08:40.793
♪ Wah-ooh-wah ♪

08:40.795 --> 08:41.994
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

08:41.996 --> 08:43.763
♪ Wah-ooh-wah ♪

08:43.765 --> 08:47.966
♪ Together we will end up
standing tall ♪

08:47.968 --> 08:50.302
♪ Together
we will stand up tall ♪

08:50.304 --> 08:54.440
♪ Together we are stronger
than a wall ♪

08:54.442 --> 08:56.609
♪ Stronger than a 10-foot wall ♪

08:56.611 --> 09:03.916
♪ Together we can work
to save us all ♪

09:03.918 --> 09:05.451
[ All cheering ]

09:05.453 --> 09:08.154
Hooray! We did it!
- Now we can have a sleepover.

09:08.156 --> 09:10.923
Who wants
to braid my hair?

09:10.925 --> 09:13.459
Oh, look!

09:13.461 --> 09:14.460
[ Squeaking ]

09:14.462 --> 09:15.995
Candice? Candice!

09:15.997 --> 09:18.096
Great to
see you again.

09:18.098 --> 09:19.665
[ Coos ]

09:19.667 --> 09:20.866
Ow.

09:20.868 --> 09:23.469
Oh, look!

09:23.471 --> 09:24.503
Oh!

09:24.505 --> 09:26.105
We're out of bags.
What do we do?!

09:26.107 --> 09:27.706
Step aside,
bozos!

09:27.708 --> 09:28.941
[ All gasp ]

09:28.943 --> 09:31.611
Welcome to the slam.

09:32.847 --> 09:34.647
♪♪

09:34.649 --> 09:36.048
[ All gasping ]

09:36.050 --> 09:38.984
Aah!

09:38.986 --> 09:40.052
Boom!

09:40.054 --> 09:42.187
[ Cheers and applause ]

09:42.189 --> 09:44.957
That's some
fine work, Brenda.

09:44.959 --> 09:46.192
Real good stuff.

09:46.194 --> 09:47.960
Ugh, don't let your eyes
drip on me, man.

09:47.962 --> 09:49.662
So,
what do you say?

09:49.664 --> 09:51.063
Sleepover time?

09:51.065 --> 09:53.632
My hair
won't braid itself.

09:53.634 --> 09:56.736
It's not our house,
so, you know, I'm into it.

09:56.738 --> 10:00.206
Yeah, it's not like
- we can leave anyway, so yeah.

10:00.208 --> 10:01.807
Sleepover time.

10:01.809 --> 10:04.543
♪♪

10:04.545 --> 10:06.645
[ Chatter ]

10:06.647 --> 10:08.013
♪♪

10:08.015 --> 10:10.483
My treasure.

10:12.053 --> 10:13.886
[ Giggling ]

10:13.888 --> 10:15.020
[ Candice chattering ]

10:15.022 --> 10:16.489
Done. - Good job, son.

10:17.425 --> 10:19.725
[ Yowls ]

10:19.727 --> 10:20.993
Why,
I oughta!

10:20.995 --> 10:22.861
Come here,
my little silly Billy.

10:22.863 --> 10:24.196
Hmm.

10:24.198 --> 10:26.532
Uh, I, uh, I don't think
your hair is braidable.

10:26.534 --> 10:27.733
[ Laughs ]

10:27.735 --> 10:28.934
Yeah.

10:28.936 --> 10:31.003
I'm glad
you decided to stay.

10:31.005 --> 10:32.505
[ Chuckles ]
Me, too.

10:32.507 --> 10:34.740
Sleepover time!
- [ Laughing ]

10:34.742 --> 10:36.242
[ Laughing ]

10:36.244 --> 10:38.177
Sleepover time!

10:38.179 --> 10:40.546
That's how nature played dirty,

10:40.548 --> 10:42.882
turning neighbor
against neighbor,

10:42.884 --> 10:46.852
but was thwarted by fools
leading folks to safe harbor.

10:46.854 --> 10:50.556
And Clarence got his wish,
lucky as a clover.

10:50.558 --> 10:55.427
The whole town was there
for his sweet, sweet sleepover.

10:55.429 --> 10:57.863
Hmm. Goodnight, my child.

10:57.865 --> 10:59.898
Sleep well.

10:59.900 --> 11:02.101
♪♪

11:03.303 --> 11:05.138
♪ Early to bed ♪

11:06.474 --> 11:09.242
♪ Early to rise ♪

11:10.144 --> 11:12.812
♪ Picking my nose ♪
